pulfalight.title: Oversize folders aren't displaying in Storage Notes.

comments.body:
Here is a storage note that is missing its container@type="volume"s
https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/AC120 . . . but actually, they would be dreadful if they showed up in the storage note because some of them are not numerical, like this: "Volume September/November 2002"

Here is a storage note that is missing its container@type="item"s: https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/AC053
(it contains items 1-21). I can't think of a case where it is really a priority to display these items at the moment; the real issue is when most things in a collection are at ReCAP but the material left at another repository is not a "box"; it appears that there may be no material at Mudd when there is.
@phoebeno Rather than splitting things out, do we need "ReCAP (rcpph): Box 1-665, Mudd (mudd): Some non-box content." or something?

I love that idea. I mean, in most collections with volumes, I think it will be more straightforward and would just look like "Volume 1-23". Items also. So people might miss the chance to be more specific there. But the oversize folders are a little ridiculous. Would it be possible to have it just say "oversize folders" if that container type is present? 
My main goal right now is simply to have "mudd" appear. But I can imagine people wanting to know WHICH volumes might be at ReCAP and which volumes here, at some point. 
In fact, all the problem volumes in AC120 are in the location "secure cage." Is that going to show up?

@phoebeno I'm not sure what the secure cage shows up as. What's the location code?

Maybe as a first pass we just do something like "ReCAP (rcpph): Box 1-665, Mudd (mudd): Oversize folders", by just making any non-box types just display the container types that are there rather than the associated numbers. So for volumes maybe it just says "Volumes" (volumes/items aren't inside boxes? I think this is only a problem when a component has no box)
Yes, some volumes are here on shelves, like a library! This solution sounds good to me. Thanks!
Oh, I didn't see the secure cage question. It gets this: container altrender="sc"
@phoebeno I don't think those will show up - presumably they should show up as "Mudd"?
Can we leave them off for now?
@phoebeno Yup, that's zero work, which is the best amount. üòÄ
